ille (1819–91) was a descendantof the Scottish Melvilles. His maternal grandfather was the revolutionary war general Peter Gansevoort (born 1749 in Albany, NY). His paternal grandfather was Maj. Thomas Melville of Boston. Irish bearers of the name claim descent from Maol Mhichíl, a chief of Síol Muireadhaigh (County Roscommon) in the 9th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Melvin","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Melville   with alternation of final <i>-l</i> and <i>-n</i>.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maoil Mhín</b> ‘descendant of the devotee of Maoilmhín’, a personal name meaning ‘gentle chieftain’."]},{"name":"Mulville","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Melville  ."]},{"name":"Mellin","meanings":["Scottish (Glamorgan): variant of   Melville  .","German: habitational name from any of various places so called.","English: variant of   Melling  ."]},{"name":"Mulvihill","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Paddy.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Maoil Mhichíl</b> ‘descendant of the devotee of (Saint) Michael’. The Anglicized form was sometimes abbreviated into   Melville  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Melville Of Fife was born about 1335, in Lasswade, Midlothian, Scotland. He married Isobel Cumin about 1359, in Fife, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1379, in Fife, Scotland, at the age of 45."},"et":{"Abt 1335–1379":"umbes 1335–1379","1321–Female":"1321–Surnud","1360–1429":"1360–1429","1335–1379":"1335–1379","1379":"1379","1335":"1335","1321":"1321","about 1359":"umbes 1359","Abt 1335":"umbes 1335","1360":"1360"